In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders addressed the recent shooting at the Tree of Life synagogue in Pittsburgh and condemned the act of anti-Semitism. She expressed the president's condolences for the victims and their families and highlighted the importance of confronting anti-Semitism in all its forms. Sanders also discussed the upcoming midterm elections and the president's efforts to bring the country together while still highlighting policy differences between the parties. She defended the president's use of rhetoric and criticized the media for blaming him for recent acts of violence. Sanders also touched on other topics such as the migrant caravan, potential border closures, the situation in Brazil, the murder of Jamal Khashoggi, and voter suppression allegations.